        "### Interpretation | Levels\n",
        "\n",
        "Spec `ct` is correct here because Real GDP has a visible deterministic trend.\n",
        "The null hypothesis is that the series contains a unit root (δ = 0).\n",
        "\n",
        "We **fail to reject H₀** - the ADF statistic is not sufficiently negative and\n",
        "the p-value exceeds 0.05. The data is consistent with a unit root.\n",
        "\n",
        "This means shocks to GDP are permanent. A recession does not reverse,\n",
        "the economy settles at a permanently lower path. The series has no fixed\n",
        "long-run mean to revert to.\n",
        "\n",
        "Running OLS on GDP in levels would produce spurious results: inflated R²,\n",
        "significant t-statistics, no genuine economic relationship.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion** -> Real GDP ~ I(1). Proceed to first differencing.\n"
